DeepSeek-V4 NVFP4 MoE support — upstream PR #25820, regenerated for v0.5.13.

Source: https://github.com/sgl-project/sglang/pull/25820
  "[NVIDIA] Support NVFP4 MoE for DeepSeek-V4" (trevor-m:dsv4-fp4)
  Captured 2026-06-12 at head f9c7cd475b (9 commits, +222/-17 across 9
  files; the two docs_new/ files are stripped here — code-only, 7 files).
  PR state at capture: OPEN, mergeable, CI pending. REGENERATE from the
  merged commit once it lands, then drop this patch when a release tag
  containing it is used (gate: recipe APPLY_DSV4_NVFP4_PR25820).

What it does:
  - model_config.py: auto-detects hybrid FP8(base)+NVFP4(experts)
    checkpoints (quant_algo=MIXED_PRECISION + moe_quant_algo=NVFP4 in
    config.json:quantization_config) -> nvfp4_moe_meta.
  - modelopt_quant.py: new HybridFp8NvFp4Config(Fp8Config) — FusedMoE
    layers route through ModelOptNvFp4FusedMoEMethod (our proven NVFP4
    MoE path), everything else through the inherited Fp8Config dispatch.
    Excluded MoE layers (MTP) fall back to Mxfp4FlashinferTrtllmMoEMethod
    (trtllm — B200-only, irrelevant while speculative is disabled).
  - deepseek_v4_hook.py: auto-selects moe_runner_backend
    flashinfer_trtllm_routed when backend == "auto". On SM121 this
    default is WRONG (trtllm-gen needs SM100; cf. sglang#26324) — our
    model profile pins moe_runner_backend=flashinfer_cutlass explicitly,
    which bypasses this hook.
  - flashinfer_trtllm.py / hash_topk.py / loader.py / deepseek_v4.py:
    gemm1 SwiGLU clamp plumbing, hash-MoE topk, loader + false-positive
    unloaded-params suppression (blockscale_swizzled placeholders).

Rebase notes (v0.5.13 vs PR base main@ec0eb6cce8): pure context drift,
no semantic conflicts — verified add/del line counts identical to the
upstream diff (156+/24-). Applies at fuzz=0 on tag v0.5.13.

Target checkpoint: nvidia/DeepSeek-V4-Flash-NVFP4 — see
roles/k8s_dgx/model_profiles/nvidia-deepseek-v4-flash-nvfp4.yml and
UPSTREAM_DSV4_BUGS.md §3/§5 for the full context. NO SM120/121 test
exists upstream (PR validated on B200 only) — first boot here is a
first-contact experiment.

Apply to: the sglang source tree at /data/sglang (tag v0.5.13), AFTER
the sm121 sgl-kernel patches, BEFORE `uv pip install ./python`.
Applied by the Dockerfile step added in dockerfile-dsv4-nvfp4.patch,
gated by recipe variable APPLY_DSV4_NVFP4_PR25820=1.

